We wanted you to be aware that we will be focusing on choir the first semester and will not be starting band. The administrative team will be doing a complete inventory of all instruments to assess the quality and quantity of school owned instruments. If you do not want to do the rent to own instrument program you signed up for, please call the elementary school and ask for Mrs. Jones. If at any time you have questions about choir class, please call Mrs. Jones. Thank you!

post_text: Beginning Wednesday, September 9th, USD #452 will be providing a free breakfast and a free lunch, Monday through Friday to any child ages 1-18. Any non school aged child who wishes to participate needs to sign up in advance. You may contact Sara Cox at sara.cox@usd452.org to sign up. Meals must be picked up at The junior/senior high school or the elementary school. Breakfast is served from 7:45-8:05 am, grab and go breakfast is served from 9:00-9:50 am and lunch is served from 11:00 am to 1:30 pm.

USD 452 Covid Policies INSIDE facilities

· Temperature check, health screening, and mask are required for anyone entering the indoor facility.

· Everyone is encouraged to maintain 6 ft. social distancing. Stadium seating will be available with limited capacity. Overflow seating in the commons will be available to view the game on TV. Seating will be on a first-come, first-serve basis.

USD 452 Covid Policies OUTSIDE facilities

· Temperature check and health screening for everyone entering the football facility. Masks are encouraged but not required for anyone attending an outdoor activity hosted by Stanton County Schools, excluding anyone participating in the activity.

· Everyone is encouraged to maintain 6 ft. social distancing. This does not apply to family groups.

Stanton County Elementary School
August 12 at 11:03 PM ·

Please remember the first day of school for Stanton County Schools is tomorrow August 13th. All students, staff, and visitors must wear a mask while indoors. If you don’t have one, the district will provide one. Additionally, the drinking fountains have been turned off. The bottle fill stations will be available and students are encouraged to bring a water bottle. If you don’t have one the district will provide one.

Remote learners need to pick up materials on Friday.

PreK does NOT start until Monday, August 17. The AM session is from 8:00 am to 11:30 am and the PM session is from 12:00 pm to 3:30 pm.

Have a great first day of school and welcome back!

Wearing a mask isn’t always easy, but it is worth it if it means getting to teach children face to face again. Please help set a positive tone for this new change. Here are a few things that might help: have your kid practice wearing a mask, pick a mask that fits their face, allow them to help pick the design, and explain the purpose for wearing the mask. (The district will provide a cloth mask with adjustable straps if you prefer.) We can do this Trojans!!!

The state board of education voted down the governor's executive order 20-58 that would have delayed the start of schools until September 9th. Therefore, schools for Stanton County will start on the regularly scheduled date of August 13th.

La junta estatal de educación rechazó la orden ejecutiva del gobernador 20-58 que habría retrasado el inicio de las escuelas hasta el 9 de septiembre. Por lo tanto, las escuelas para el Condado de Stanton comenzarán en la fecha programada regularmente del 13 de agosto.

post_text:
STANTON COUNTY SUMMER LUNCH PROGRAM CHANGES STARTING MONDAY, JUNE 15TH

With the next re-opening phase, the summer lunch program will also move forward! We are SO excited to say hello to all our kids!

1. To receive a lunch, the child/youth must be present. Parents can not pick up a meal without the child being present.

2. Pre-packed individual meals and Family Quick Pick Up meals will end.

3. Kids will line up outside - social distancing will be encouraged.

4. A volunteer will greet the kids at The Old Store door – Five (5) kids will be allowed into the store at a time to walk through a buffet line.

5. Once the child has received their meal, they will exit the store and should return home to eat their meal.

6. A Friday meal will continue to be handed out on Thursday. The number of meals will be limited to the amount of leftovers we have available. First Come/First Serve.

We have missed seeing all our kid's smiling faces and are so excited for Monday!

A partir del viernes 17 de abril, el programa de alimentación escolar cambiará un poco. Todavía vamos a enviar comidas de lunes a viernes. Pero solo vamos a repartir comidas los martes y viernes.

Entonces, para aclarar, así es como distribuiremos nuestras comidas:

Viernes- 2 desayunos y 2 almuerzos
Lunes y martes desayuno
Viernes y lunes almuerzos

Martes- 3 desayunos y 3 almuerzos
Desayunos miércoles, jueves y viernes
Martes, miércoles y jueves almuerzos

Aún recibirá 5 desayunos y 5 almuerzos cada semana si recoge los dos días.

Seguiremos estableciendo en Big Bow, Manter, SCHS y gestionando las rutas de los autobuses, pero solo los martes y viernes.

post_text:
Starting Friday April 17 the school food program is going to change a little. We are still going to be sending out meals for Monday through Friday. But we are only going to be handing out meals on Tuesdays and Fridays.

So just to clarify this is how we will be distributing our meals:

Fridays- 2 breakfast and 2 lunches

Monday and Tuesdays breakfast

Friday and Mondays lunches

Tuesday- 3 breakfast and 3 lunches

Wednesday, Thursday and Fridays breakfasts

Tuesday, Wednesday and Thursdays lunches

You will still be receiving 5 breakfast and 5 lunches each week if you pick up on both days.

We will still be setting up at Big Bow, Manter, SCHS and running the bus routes but only on Tuesdays and Fridays.

As of 12:01 am on Monday, March 30th, Kansas will be under a stay at home order. Randy Watson, the commissioner of education, just announced that this will not impact the Continuous Learning Plans that have been developed. This means no changes for Stanton County Schools. Virtual learning will start on Monday, March 30th as planned.

A partir de las 12:01 am del lunes 30 de marzo, Kansas estará bajo una orden de permanencia en el hogar. Randy Watson, el comisionado de educación, acaba de anunciar que esto no afectará los planes de aprendizaje continuo que se han desarrollado. Esto significa que no hay cambios para las Escuelas del Condado de Stanton. El aprendizaje virtual comenzará el lunes 30 de marzo según lo planeado.

ATTENTION SCES FAMILIES!!!

Tomorrow, March 26th will be our curbside pick-up for your child’s chromebook, textbooks, resources, and personal items. Please pull up to the front of the elementary school and wait in your car until nobody is at the table. You will be given a box with your child’s items. Please pay close attention to the following time schedule. See you tomorrow!

9:00 am - 10:00 am: Last names from A to E

10:00 am - 11:00 am: Last names from F to J

11:00 am - 12:00 pm: Last names from K to O

1:00 pm - 2:00 pm: Last names from P to T

2:00 pm - 3:00 pm: Last names from U to Z

If you cannot pick up your items due to a quarantine or other reasons, please call 620-492-6216 and we will deliver them to your porch.

Please pull up to the front of the elementary school and wait in your car until nobody is at the table. You will be given a box with your child’s items. Please pay close attention to the following time schedule. See you tomorrow!

9:00 am - 10:00 am: Last names from A to E

10:00 am - 11:00 am: Last names from F to J

11:00 am - 12:00 pm: Last names from K to O

1:00 pm - 2:00 pm: Last names from P to T

2:00 pm - 3:00 pm: Last names from U to Z

If you cannot pick up your items due to a quarantine or other reasons, please call 620-492-6216 and we will deliver them to your porch.

Gracias a Pioneer Communications por instalar un punto de acceso wifi en el estacionamiento de High School. Los estudiantes y la comunidad pueden usarlo siempre que practique un distanciamiento social seguro.

Pedimos que la comunidad respete el uso de los estudiantes primero, mientras que Pioneer trabaja para que Internet llegue a sus hogares, esta puede ser la única forma en que pueden hacer su tarea durante el cierre de la escuela Covid-19 (Coronavirus).

Recuerde que esta sigue siendo una conexión filtrada, así que úsela SOLAMENTE para uso apropiado para la escuela.

Nuevamente, gracias a Pioneer Communications por proporcionar este servicio comunitario en este momento de necesidad.

post_text:
¡Hola desde el lejano suroeste de Kansas! Solo quiero alardear de estas 3 damas que trabajan sin parar en nuestra cocina Y nuestros conductores de autobuses del distrito. Hoy servimos 204 desayunos y 204 almuerzos. Estamos sirviendo en 3 ubicaciones Johnson City, Manter y Big Bow. Estas damas están preparando todas las comidas. Salir y servirlos a todos los niños. Luego regresando y limpiando y preparando para el día siguiente. Y también enviando comidas en 2 rutas de autobús. ¡Muchísimas gracias a nuestros conductores de autobuses por llevar las comidas a aquellos niños que no pueden llegar a uno de estos lugares! ¡Debo decir que este equipo realmente está mostrando nuestros valores centrales de OPAA! Están 'Actuando en el mejor interés de nuestros estudiantes, la escuela y nuestra comunidad'. Y realmente puedes ver 'Su pasión por servir a los demás'.

¡Nos estamos asegurando de que los niños reciban alimento y 'Haciendo Su Día' aquí en Southwest KS!

Sara Cox

Director de servicios de nutrición

Distrito del condado de Stanton 452

620.453.9184

scox@opaafood.com

post_text:
Hello from far Southwest Kansas! I am just wanting to brag on these 3 ladies working their tails off in our kitchen AND our district bus drivers. Today we served 204 breakfast and 204 lunches. We are serving in 3 locations Johnson City, Manter and Big Bow. These ladies are preparing all the meals. Going out and serving them to all kids. Then coming back and cleaning up and prepping for the next day. And also sending meals out on 2 bus routes. A HUGE thanks to our bus drivers for getting the meals out to those that kids that can't make it into 1 of these locations! I have to say this crew is really showing our OPAA core values! They are 'Acting in the best interest of our students, school and our community'. And you can really see 'Their passion to serve others'.

We are making sure kids are getting feed and 'Making Their Day' out here in Southwest KS!

Sara Cox

Director of Nutrition Services

Stanton County District 452

620.453.9184

scox@opaafood.com

Stanton County Jr/Sr High School
March 23 at 12:41 AM ·

Reminder: No School March 23-27

Spring Break has been extended to allow administration, teachers, and staff time to develop a plan so our Trojans can finish out the school year strong!

*Don’t forget, the Grab & Go breakfast and Lunch program starts tomorrow! It is FREE to ALL children 1-18 years old and you can still sign up or at any time by email or text to opaa@usd452.org (Yes, you can text to this email address) Just include your first/last name, how many meals for children, and which site you will pick up at. Pick up is available at SCHS, Manter school, or Big Bow at the corner of Big Bow Grade and Fourth Ave.

post_text: El Gobernador de Kansas ha ordenado que todas las escuelas de Kansas estén cerradas a las actividades normales hasta finales de mayo. Esto no significa que no haya escuela. Todos los estudiantes estarán fuera de la escuela la próxima semana. La facultad y el personal de USD 452 se reunirán la próxima semana para desarrollar un plan de aprendizaje continuo que se implementará durante el resto del año escolar. KSDE proporciona orientación en el desarrollo del plan de aprendizaje continuo. El plan puede incluir aprendizaje en línea, paquetes de papel enviados a casa, aprendizaje en grupos pequeños en la escuela o cualquier otra estrategia desarrollada por la facultad y el personal aprobada por KSDE como parte del plan de aprendizaje continuo. Busque información esta noche o mañana en la oficina del superintendente.

post_text: Kansas Governor has mandated all schools in Kansas be closed to normal activities until the end of May. This doesn’t mean there is no school. All students will be out of school next week. Faculty and staff of USD 452 will meet next week to develop a continual learning plan to be implemented for the remainder of the school year. Guidance in the development of the continual learning plan is being provided by KSDE. The plan can include online learning, paper packets sent home, small group learning at the school or any other strategy developed by the faculty and staff that is approved by KSDE as part of the continual learning plan. Look for information tonight or tomorrow from the superintendent’s office.

shared_text:
Stanton County USD 452
March 15 at 11:13 PM ·

Effective Monday, March 16, all spring sports and activities are suspended through Sunday, March 22.

This includes cancellation of all practices and competitions for this week.

This prohibition is consistent with KSDE and governmental guidance and may be extended, should conditions warrant. Please note spring sports team members are prohibited from club or outside team participation and practice during this period. Not only would such outside participation be contrary to handbook rule, it would be contrary to the very reason activities are cancelled during the time we seek to mitigate potential transfer of the contagion.

shared_text:
Stanton County Jr/Sr High School
March 2 at 8:30 PM ·

Dear Parents/Guardians,

This Wednesday, March 4, our 7-12th grade students will be traveling to Lakin for a presentation. The presenter will be former NBA player, Chris Herren. Mr. Herren will be speaking about the dangers of substance abuse, and he will be sharing from his life experiences.

The students and staff will be leaving at 8:30 a.m. and will be returning to the school at around 1:00 p.m. This will be considered a normal day of school, so if they are not going to attend, they need to be excused by a parent. Sack lunches will be taken, or students have been given the option to bring their own lunch.

If you have any questions, please contact Mr. Siebert at the HS office 620-492-6284.

Thank you!

Stanton County KS FFA
February 29 at 5:14 AM ·

Great FFA Week activity-Town Tag. (Thanks to Kiowa County FFA for the idea.)These are the only pictures I have from Town Tag tonight-advisor fail!!! We had about 60 kids that worked in teams to make it from the high school to the Battin Park sign and back without getting tagged! The kids were excited all week and want to do it again. Thanks to our taggers Jeff and Azuree Jones, Jim Sipes, Liz Harms, Trenton Horn, Trevor and Rachelle Siebert, and Donnie Morgan. We had several others in town that volunteered to “tag” and that was greatly appreciated. (We will contact you again.) This will be marked down as a win!

Tonight was an exciting night because we had the opportunity to recognize our recent State Championships! The banners have been hung and added to the gym wall for the 2019 Boys State Track Champs, 2019 Girls State Cross Country Champs, and 2019 Boys State Cross Country Champs! We are proud of the Trojans and their coaches! Also, Congratulations to Peyton Peterson and Yessenia Ornelas on earning the Cross Country Academic All-State Honor!

And finally, a HUGE congratulations to Coach Mike Horton on being named the 2A Cross Country Coach is the Year and the All-Class Cross Country Coach is the year!

December 9, 2019 at 9:47 PM ·

PARA-PROFESSIONAL POSITION



USD #452, Stanton County Schools has openings for Para-Professional.

Candidates must have the ability to communicate and work cooperatively with students, staff, and the ability to work without direct supervision.

Qualifications: Bilingual preferred, High School diploma or GED, sixty college hours, or pass the Para-Pro test. Benefits include KPERS retirement, participation in district health insurance and paid leave. Salary is commensurate with experience and qualifications. Applications available at the USD 452 District Office, or by calling 620-492-6226. Position is open until filled.
